## Source of Truth

**Hierarchy (inverted — auto-loaded wins):**

1. **`.claude/rules/*`** — authoritative for coding conventions and app patterns. Auto-loaded every session.
2. **CLAUDE.md (this file)** — project hub and routing. High-level only; defer implementation detail to rules.
3. **`method/sop/*`** — deep reference. Demand-loaded.

If CLAUDE.md and a rules file conflict on implementation detail, the rules file wins. If a rules file and an SOP conflict, raise it — one of them is drifting.

## VBW Rules

- Plans reference CLAUDE.md conventions. VBW agents follow them during execution.
- Skills are for interactive sessions, not agent execution paths.
- All VBW artifacts live in `.vbw-planning/`. Agents do not modify product code without a plan.
- Agents must validate against the pre-deploy gate before marking work complete.
- Do not invoke VBW agents directly in Pipekit projects. Use `/launch`, not `/vbw:lead` / `/vbw:dev`. `/launch` wraps VBW and keeps Linear/PHASES.md/NEXT.md in sync.

See `method/method.md` § "VBW / Pipekit Ownership Model" for details.
